3 (13) “NONPROFIT CIVIL RIGHTS ORGANIZATION” MEANS:
4 (I) A QUALIFIED FAIR HOUSING ENFORCEMENT
5 ORGANIZATION OR A FAIR HOUSING ORGANIZATION AS DEFINED UNDER 24 C.F.R. §
6 125.103; OR
7 (II) AN ORGANIZATION INCORPORATED UNDER MARYLAND
8 LAW AS A PRIVATE, TAX–EXEMPT CIVIL RIGHTS ORGANIZATION THAT HAS AT LEAST
9 2 YEARS’ EXPERIENCE IN:
10 1. COMPLAINT INTAKE;
11 2. COMPLAINT INVESTIGATION; AND
12 3. TESTING FOR FAIR HOUSING VIOLATIONS OR
13 ENFORCEMENT OF MERITORIOUS CLAIMS.
14 [(13)] (14) (i) “Oral communication” means any conversation or words
15 spoken to or by any person in private conversation.
16 (ii) “Oral communication” does not include any electronic
17 communication.
18 [(14)] (15) “Person” means any employee or agent of this State or a political
19 subdivision thereof, and any individual, partnership, association, joint stock company,
20 trust, or corporation.
21 [(15)] (16) “Readily accessible to the general public” means, with respect to
22 a radio communication, that the communication is not:
23 (i) Scrambled or encrypted;
24 (ii) Transmitted using modulation techniques the essential
25 parameters of which have been withheld from the public with the intention of preserving
26 the privacy of the communication; or
27 (iii) Except for tone–only paging device communications, transmitted
28 over frequencies reserved for private use and licensed for private use under federal or State
29 law.
30 [(16)] (17) “Telephone solicitation theft” means conduct of a person that:

