1 (i) Constitutes the offense of theft or attempted theft; and
2 (ii) Involves the use of a telephone to solicit the payment of money.
3 [(17)] (18) “User” means any person or entity that:
4 (i) Uses an electronic communication service; and
5 (ii) Is duly authorized by the provider of the service to engage in that
6 use.
7 [(18)] (19) “Wire communication” means any aural transfer made in whole
8 or in part through the use of facilities for the transmission of communications by the aid of
9 wire, cable, or other like connection between the point of origin and the point of reception
10 (including the use of a connection in a switching station) furnished or operated by any
11 person licensed to engage in providing or operating such facilities for the transmission of
12 communications.
13 10–402.
14 (c) (12) (I) IT IS LAWFUL UNDER THIS SUBTITLE FOR A PERSON TO
15 INTERCEPT AN ORAL COMMUNICATION IF:
16 1. THE PERSON IS WORKING AS A FAIR HOUSING TESTER
17 FOR A FAIR HOUSING TESTING PROGRAM OPERATED BY:
18 A. THE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT;
19 B. THE STATE;
20 C. A LOCAL GOVERNMENT; OR
21 D. A NONPROFIT CIVIL RIGHTS ORGANIZATION;
22 2. THE PERSON IS A PARTY TO THE COMMUNICATION;
23 AND
24 3. THE INTERCEPTION IS BEING MADE FOR THE
25 PURPOSE OF OBTAINING EVIDENCE OF A FAIR HOUSING VIOLATION UNDER
26 FEDERAL, STATE, OR LOCAL LAW.
27 (II) EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN SUBPARAGRAPH (III) OF THIS
28 PARAGRAPH, NO PART OF THE CONTENTS OF THE INTERCEPTED COMMUNICATION
29 AND NO EVIDENCE DERIVED THEREFROM MAY BE RECEIVED IN EVIDENCE IN ANY
30 TRIAL, HEARING, OR OTHER PROCEEDING IN OR BEFORE ANY COURT, GRAND JURY,

4 SENATE BILL 107
1 DEPARTMENT, OFFICER, AGENCY, REGULATORY BODY, LEGISLATIVE COMMITTEE,
2 OR OTHER AUTHORITY OF THE STATE OR A POLITICAL SUBDIVISION OF THE STATE.
3 (III) THE CONTENTS OF AN INTERCEPTED ORAL
4 COMMUNICATION MADE IN ACCORDANCE WITH SUBPARAGRAPH (I) OF THIS
5 PARAGRAPH MAY BE USED ONLY FOR THE PURPOSE OF ENFORCING FEDERAL,
6 STATE, OR LOCAL FAIR HOUSING LAWS.
7 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
8 October 1, 2025.
